WEBVTT

0
00:00:01.360 --> 00:00:01.679
Next,

1
00:00:01.759 --> 00:00:03.119
we'll create a discussion board.

2
00:00:05.210 --> 00:00:07.050
Click the plus button under the header,

3
00:00:07.170 --> 00:00:09.079
then create button and then discussion.

4
00:00:09.449 --> 00:00:10.949
The discussion homepage will appear.

5
00:00:12.109 --> 00:00:13.510
Change the name of the assignment to

6
00:00:13.510 --> 00:00:16.170
one that students will easily recognize and then

7
00:00:16.389 --> 00:00:18.409
type in the topic the students will address.

8
00:00:20.180 --> 00:00:22.459
As with the rest of Blackboard's content tools,

9
00:00:22.670 --> 00:00:24.809
instructors may type in their own topic

10
00:00:25.069 --> 00:00:27.030
or have one auto generated for them

11
00:00:27.250 --> 00:00:28.540
based on the course content.

12
00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:31.979
From there,

13
00:00:32.049 --> 00:00:34.520
click the gear icon on the top right-hand side.

14
00:00:36.979 --> 00:00:38.240
This is the settings menu

15
00:00:39.220 --> 00:00:39.500
Here,

16
00:00:39.580 --> 00:00:43.180
instructors may select various options such as posting first,

17
00:00:43.380 --> 00:00:44.409
editing posts,

18
00:00:44.610 --> 00:00:45.919
grading and due dates.

19
00:00:55.250 --> 00:00:55.950
For this example,

20
00:00:56.130 --> 00:00:59.090
we will click display on course content page to

21
00:00:59.090 --> 00:01:01.169
ensure the assignment shows up on the homepage,

22
00:01:01.450 --> 00:01:03.009
not just the discussions page.

23
00:01:03.700 --> 00:01:05.019
We will click post first,

24
00:01:05.099 --> 00:01:07.879
so students must post their initial response to the question

25
00:01:08.379 --> 00:01:10.040
before seeing their classmates work.

26
00:01:13.699 --> 00:01:14.800
Under great discussion,

27
00:01:14.980 --> 00:01:16.879
we can set 2 separate due dates.

28
00:01:18.449 --> 00:01:20.709
So students know when the initial post

29
00:01:20.849 --> 00:01:22.330
and the response posts are due.

30
00:01:25.910 --> 00:01:27.910
Set the grade category for the grade book,

31
00:01:28.230 --> 00:01:29.459
the points for the assignment,

32
00:01:29.550 --> 00:01:32.989
and instructors can create their own rubric or auto generate one.

33
00:01:34.580 --> 00:01:35.599
Then click save